        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 7:54PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 753 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Newland, or near Sugar Mountain, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newland, Banner Elk, Sugar Mountain, Seven Devils, Grandfather
Mountain State Park, and Minneapolis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
